#Text=Choose a Name for a Pet
#Text=It is estimated that 35-47 % of American households own dogs , and 30-37 % own cats .
#Text=These numbers do not even include other household pets ! Owning a pet is one thing , but it is another thing to think of a unique name .
#Text=If you are planning on bringing home a new member of the family , you may be wondering how to choose the perfect name .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Picking a Name Based On Your Pet
#Text=Evaluate pet appearance .
#Text=What your pet looks like may a good place to start when you want to name your new pet .
#Text=Consider things like :
#Text=Fur color or length .
#Text=( For example , if you own a long-hair dog or cat , you can name it " Shaggy " . )
#Text=Distinguishing colored patches .
#Text=( For example , you may name your pet " Boots " if it has color patches on his/her paws . )
#Text=Distinguishing features or injuries
#Text=Eye color ( For example , you may name your pet " Frankie " after Frank Sinatra , whose nickname was " Ol ' Blue Eyes .
#Text=Identify pet personality .
#Text=How your pet acts may be another great way to pick the perfect name .
#Text=Observe your pet to distinguish unique characteristics
#Text=Unique vocalizations ( bark , meow , squeak , etc ) .
#Text=( For example , if your cat has a quiet meow , you may name it " Silence " )
#Text=Temperament such as happiness or sleepiness .
#Text=( " Happy , " " Sleepy , " " Peaceful , " " Bossy , " or " Cranky " might be good names . )
#Text=Consider your pet ’s uniqueness .
#Text=Some of the best names can come from the pet ’s uniqueness .
#Text=If your pet comes has an interesting background , consider it when picking a name .
#Text=Ask yourself :
#Text=Did my pet come from a unique or far-away location ?
#Text=Consider naming it after a city or country such as Cleveland or Italy .
#Text=Did my pet come from a specific family or shelter ?
#Text=Think about a name after the person you adopted your pet from , maybe like " Sherry " or " Lisa .

#Text=Famous dogs include  Checkers " ( Nixon 's dog ) and " Sunny " ( Obama 's dog ) .

column1: #Text=Famous cats include Hemingway 's cat " Boise " and President Lincoln 's cat " Tabby .
#Text=Skip long or complicated names .
#Text=If you want your pet to recognize its name , it is best to stick to short names that are easy to pronounce .
#Text=You may want to avoid names like Mississippi , Sacramento , Fitzgerald .
#Text=If you like the sound of a long name , consider abbreviating it ( Missi , Mento , Fitz ) .
#Text=Stay away from inappropriate or rude names .
#Text=You will be using this name on documents .
#Text=You will be calling your pet this name in public and others will have to say it as well .
#Text=Stay away from offensive names and stick with something that can be heard or read by all .
#Text=Avoid names that include curse words or bodily functions .
#Text=Quick Summary
